Content:
I&#x27;ve never practiced eastern philosophy, but it&#x27;s not surprising that people arrive at the same conclusions on psychedelics.
See, psychedelic plants/fungi  have been around since before humans and people who took them, say, 3000 years ago had the same trips and the same realisations that we have today.
Then they came back and wrote about their conclusions, which has sometimes led to the creations of new philosophies or religions.<p>This is one other realisation that you have while tripping - &quot;I have been in this state before, many times before, but not in this body, I was a yogi in India or a shaman in South America or a philosopher in ancient Greece and I&#x27;ve always remembered: I am. It&#x27;s always been me.&quot;
